        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 4:34PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Bliss, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Central El Paso, East El Paso, Northeast El Paso, Far East El Paso,
Mission Valley, Horizon City, Fort Bliss, Biggs Field, Fort Bliss
Northeast, Franklin Mountains State Park, and McKelligon Canyon.

This includes Interstate 10 in Texas between mile markers 20 and 34.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
